            <handDesc>
              <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                <seg type="rubrication">
                  <ref target="#ms_i1.1 #ms_i1.2"/>
                  <desc>Psalm headings and numbers are rubricated in , headings are rubricated in
                       The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word
                    Mary is rubricated in the final two works </desc>
                </seg>
                <desc>Columetric layout of text: <ref type="item" target="#ms_i1.2"/><locus target="#113r #113v #114r" facs="113 114"/>
                  <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1566hababa#ThreeYouths3">Third Song of the Three Youths in the Furnace,  ThreeYouths3</ref>
                </desc>
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <decoDesc>
              <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#1r" facs="001"/><desc>A box
                  with three panels: above two <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref>s blow
                  trumpets; in the middle there are five arches; below is a crowd of people. The
                  miniature is clearly painted over text</desc></decoNote>
              <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2"> Decorative designs: <locus target="#99v" facs="100"/> (crude ḥaräg); <locus target="#4r #11v #21r #28r #34r #42v #54r #61v #67r #79r #93v #105r #117r" facs="004 012 021 028 034 043 054 062 067 079 094 105 117"/> (a line of
                alternating red and black dots with multiple full stops); <locus target="#90v" facs="091"/> (multiple full stops) </decoNote>
            </decoDesc>
            <additions>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="e1">
                  <desc> Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1v #8r #44r #45r" facs="002 008 044 045"/>, etc.); lines of text are
                    written interlinearly (<locus target="#13v #16r #50v #75v" facs="014 016 051 076"/>, etc.); lines of text are written in the upper margin
                    with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#47r" facs="047"> f. 47r, line 4</locus>;<locus target="#92r" facs="092"> f. 92r, line 10</locus>;<locus target="#117v" facs="118"> f. 117v,
                      line 17</locus>); text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#9r #23v #43r #65r" facs="009 024 043 065"/>) </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="e2">
                  <desc> This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one
                    line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the width of most
                    lines. On a few occasions, the line would have been too long and the scribe
                    finishes the end of the line with words written smaller so as to avoid leftover
                    text (e.g., <locus target="#38r #58v #61v" facs="038 059 062"/>). Occasionally a
                    line is still too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the
                    line (e.g., <locus target="#18r #20v #21r" facs="018 021"/>) </desc>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
            <bindingDesc>
              <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, 190 x 172 x 50 mm, four Coptic chain stitches
                  attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood,
                  covered with red linen with intricate four-leaf and circular patterns, remnant of
                  headband and tailband visible.</decoNote>
                <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                  <material key="parchment"/>
                  <material key="wood"/>
                  <material key="textile"/>
                </decoNote>
              </binding>
            </bindingDesc>
